data.title: davinahalliwell-winchester
data.meta_description: Follow @davinahalliwell-winchester and get more of the good stuff by joining Tumblr today. Dive in!
data.text:
This entire episode with them was just one of the most intense and hottest scenes I’ve ever watched. And props to Kassie Depaiva and Roger Howarth for proving that older couples can be hot too, it doesn’t always have to teens and twenty-somethings!

I couldn’t resist using this scene. I love this speech of Todd’s and, even though he has a few that I also love, this one sticks out because it’s one of the few time he actually tells Blair how he feels about her in the earlier years.

I just think this scene sums up TnB perfectly. A little bit too wild and a little bit too free. I love how Blair says they tame each other and love each other no matter what because that’s just very true to their relationship. I think this is Blair at her most honest, she’s not talking to another person with their own thoughts and opinions on her and Todd’s relationship, she doesn’t know that Todd’s behind her, she’s just expressing herself.

I debated between using Dorian for this one or yesterday’s but ultimately I don’t really consider Dorian a TnB enemy because she does love Blair even if hates Todd however I do consider her a third party solely because of how many times she inserts herself into their relationship.

Ah, Max Holden. I had to use Max for this prompt. I just feel like Max is the only enemy that actually gives Todd and Blair a run for their money and even gets the upper hand on them sometimes.

Ah, the scheme that started it all. It’s not a TnB scheme, Todd was decidedly not involved in this scheme but without this scheme we wouldn’t have TnB at all.
